approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

available().notice: Defines how much of the Setts' underlying can be borrowed by the Strategy for useCustom logic in here for how much the vault allows to be borrowedSets minimum required on-hand to keep small withdrawals cheap

balance().notice: Return the total balance of the underlying token within the systemSums the balance in the Sett, the Controller, and the Strategy

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation. For example, if `decimals` equals `2`, a balance of `505` tokens should be displayed to a user as `5,05` (`505 / 10 ** 2`). Tokens usually opt for a value of 18, imitating the relationship between Ether and Wei. This is the value {ERC20} uses, unless {_setupDecimals} is called. NOTE: This information is only used for _display_ purposes: it in no way affects any of the arithmetic of the contract, including {IERC20-balanceOf} and {IERC20-transfer}.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `subtractedValue`.

deposit(uint256).notice: Deposit assets into the Sett, and return corresponding shares to the userOnly callable by EOA accounts that pass the _defend() check

depositAll().notice: Convenience function: Deposit entire balance of asset into the Sett, and return corresponding shares to the userOnly callable by EOA accounts that pass the _defend() check

earn().notice: Transfer the underlying available to be claimed to the controllerThe controller will deposit into the Strategy for yield-generating activitiesPermissionless operation

harvest(address,uint256).notice: Used to swap any borrowed reserve over the debt limit to liquidate to 'token'Only controller can trigger harvests

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

setController(address).notice: Change controller addressCan only be changed by governance

setGovernance(address).notice: Change governance addressCan only be changed by governance itself

setKeeper(address).notice: Change keeper addressCan only be changed by governance itself

setMin(uint256).notice: Set minimum threshold of underlying that must be deposited in strategyCan only be changed by governance

setStrategist(address).notice: Change strategist addressCan only be changed by governance itself

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

trackFullPricePerShare().details: Emit event tracking current full price per shareProvides a pure on-chain way of approximating APY

transfer(address,uint256).details: Add blockLock to transfers, users cannot transfer tokens in the same block as a deposit or withdrawal.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}; Requirements: - `sender` and `recipient` cannot be the zero address. - `sender` must have a balance of at least `amount`. - the caller must have allowance for ``sender``'s tokens of at least `amount`.

withdraw(uint256).notice: No rebalance implementation for lower fees and faster swaps

withdrawAll().notice: Convenience function: Withdraw all shares of the sender
